Really wanting to play the Switch remake, but have never owned or played the original Gameboy or DX version until today. I'm a huge Link to the Past fan, so am really stoked to finally have the opportunity to play this one

The Legend of Zelda: Link's Awakening is a 1993 action-adventure game developed and published by Nintendo for the Game Boy. It was the first installment in The Legend of Zelda series for a handheld game console.

Link's Awakening was critically and commercially successful. Critics praised the game's depth and number of features; complaints focused on its control scheme and monochrome graphics. An updated re-release titled The Legend of Zelda: Link's Awakening DX was released for the Game Boy Color in 1998 featuring color graphics, compatibility with the Game Boy Printer, and an exclusive color-based dungeon. Together, the two versions of the game have sold more than six million units worldwide, and have appeared on multiple game publications' lists of the best video games of all time. A remake of the game was released for the Nintendo Switch in September 2019. (Source @wikipedia)

‘Zelda - Link’s Awakening’, gold foil screen print edition.
-
Released inline with the reimagined Link’s Awakening for Nintendo Switch, we produced these officially licensed @nintendo screen prints as a @zavviuk exclusive.
-
The print, designed by @suzsinhell, depicts the map of the mythical island of Koholint, where the game takes place (albeit entirely inside the Wind Fish’s dream). It’s a captivating image, and highly shiny gold foil by @mirriuk makes the whole thing that extra bit special.
-
Link’s Awakening is an A2 edition of 200 + AP’s, printed 1/1 onto 290gsm Mirri Gold foil, with black ink on front and metallic gold on the reverse, where you’ll find the official @nintendo Seal of Quality.
-
It’s a beauty!

caption.text:
The awesome people at Microsoft sent me an early copy of Ori and the Blind Forest for Nintendo Switch. Been playing since last night and it’s absolutely incredible. It’s just as good as you remember but now on a new, potentially more convenient platform. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
One of the biggest worries is obviously performance, seeing as this was originally an XB1 game. Thankfully nothing has been comprised with this port at all. Game runs flawlessly. The visuals are still just as stunning as before but now you can also play it on a handheld. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Speaking of handheld. This game is just perfect in portable mode. It’s easy to pick up and play in quick bursts with a very intuitive save system. Or you can do what I do and just get super lost into the game while wearing a pair of headphones while laying comfortably in bed. ⁣
⁣⁣
The developers made a lot of improvements to their engine since the original release so this version should technically be more refined as well. For example, Ori’s sprites actually animate at 60fps now vs the 30fps sprite animations of the original. You can see the difference pretty clearly when you play the game. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
If you never played Ori when it first came out you owe it to yourself to check this game out. It’s a fun, challenging game with amazing visuals and an awesome soundtrack. If you played this game before it’s also worth revisiting before the sequel releases next year. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣

caption.text:
A break from Smash Ultimate feels exactly what I needed. I really thought I didn’t have enough passion to compete in this game anymore but I guess I just needed a bit of a breather because now I feel otherwise :)
.
Like I said in my last post, I really do love being part of the Smash community and the competitive scene. I feel more apart of this community than I ever did back in the COD community a few years ago.
.
Smash is my game and that’s that! This is my shit guys. I know I can be one of the best. I was improving a lot before this little break so I believe in my ability to learn, get better and grow as a player more than ever.
.
I will also be sticking with Pokemon Trainer and going back to Daisy/Peach. Those are my two best characters and the characters I enjoy the most in this game.
.
And while I may be getting back on the grind, I’m going to work on pacing myself better so the game doesn’t stress me out. Both life-wise and game-wise. Exercising then meditating every morning has been a big help in my mindset and my mood so I’ve been feeling a lot better lately.
.
I’ll be much more prepared, especially mentally, when I start attending tournaments again. Your boy boutta transcend this time around. 🙇🏻‍♂️
.
Also content and streams will be resuming soon. 😉
.
Why do you play the games you play? Why do you play video games?

caption.text:
I’ve been steadily picking at 'Fire Emblem Three Houses' for the past month or so and while I admit I haven’t quite finished the game I can say confidently that it is one of my favorites of the year. While I don’t have a ton of experience with the Fire Emblem series it's hard to imagine the diehards finding too much at fault with it’s core gameplay. The turn based “rock paper scissors” battles the series is iconic for are so engaging and addictive to play and beautifully presented. There’s something so epic about having the camera rapidly zoom in to the ground level of the battlefield so you can watch your characters duke it out. But I think the crowning achievement of this game is its story and narrative structure. You play as “The Professor” a sort of blank slate character who finds him or herself teaching at a prestigious military academy. In between battles you will fill your time lecturing and getting to know your students (who of course are your soldiers in battles) all the while completing side quests around the school. It’s essentially a lighter but more focused version of what the Persona series does. Within the first couple hours of play I found myself really caring for my students and motivated to prepare them as effectively as I could so they wouldn’t die in combat (yes perma-death is still a thing if you want it). This along with a storyline that evolves and twists based on your actions and choices makes for an immensely satisfying narrative experience. Excellent gameplay, excellent story, excellent game.
.
.

Mas e se fosse uma luminária?
.

.

.
Obs.: ao apertar 100 vezes você não ganha uma vida extra.
.

Link é o nome dado a uma série de encarnações de um mesmo personagem fictício, protagonista da série The Legend of Zelda da Nintendo. Criada por Shigeru Miyamoto, a série faz sucesso e já recebeu, além dos jogos, mangás e até uma série de desenho animado.

Link é retratado como um jovem (variando de 10 a 18 anos). Ele é da raça fictícia Hylian, que é muito parecida com a raça elfo da floresta. Link não emite nenhum diálogo nos jogos, apenas emitindo grunhidos característicos de luta. O objetivo principal de Link normalmente é salvar Hyrule e a Princesa Zelda do antagonista da série, Ganon, usando a Master Sword. Entretanto, isso não é uma regra, já que em alguns jogos, ele enfrenta situações completamente diferentes (em Minish Cap, Four Swords e Four Swords Adventures, Link enfrenta Vaati usando a lendária Four Sword; em Majora's Mask, ele deve salvar a terra de Termina de uma lua criada pelo antagonista do jogo, que está prestes a cair). Os pais de Link quase nunca são mencionados, e nunca aparecem diretamente nos jogos. Em algumas encarnações, porém, Link vive com outros membros da família. Um exemplo disso é A Link to the Past, no qual Link vive com seu tio em uma pequena casa. Além disso, Link, em The Legend of Zelda: Twilight Princess, é transformado em um sagrado lobo, sendo necessária a transformação para o desenvolvimento da história.

Link é considerado um dos personagens mais influentes no mundo dos games, reaparecendo como um lutador em diversos jogos, tais como Super Smash Bros., Super Smash Bros. Melee (onde há a sua versão jovem, Young Link, vinda de The Legend of Zelda: Ocarina of Time), Super Smash Bros. Brawl (onde aparece uma versão cartunesca sua, Toon Link, vinda de The Legend of Zelda: The Wind Waker), Soul Calibur II e Super Smash Bros. para Nintendo 3DS e Wii U.

•

Con la ayuda de sus amigos, Takuya debe descubrir el misterio del legado de su padre, un investigador que ha llevado a cabo diversos estudios sobre astrofísica y que desapareció en extrañas circunstancias.

1993
GIOCAVO CON IL MIO GB GRIGIO A TETRIS.
UN MIO AMICO, NON RICORDO ESATTAMENTE, MI DISSE
"IO QUESTO GIOCO NON LO CAPISCO, FACCIAMO CAMBIO CHE IO A TETRIS NON CI HO MAI GIOCATO?"
ALLORCHÉ, INGENUAMENTE, GLI DISSI DI NO.
QUALCHE GIORNO DOPO, SEMPRE LUI "DAI, ANGELO, FACCIAMO CAMBIO SOLO PER UNA SETTIMANA" STANCO DELLE SUE LAMENTELE (ERO SOCIOPATICO GIÀ DALLA TENERA ETÀ) ACCONSENTII.
IL GIOCO ERA "THE LEGEND OF ZELDA - LINK'S AWAKENING".
QUESTO OMINO CHE GIRAVA A ZONZO PER QUESTA ISOLA CON UNA SPADA E UNO SCUDO.
"MA CHE CACATA È QUESTA" PENSAI.
DOPO AVER FINITO I COMPITI, QUEL GIORNO, MI RIMISI A GIOCARE. 
DOPO UN'ORETTA BUONA, AVEVO CAPITO LA MECCANICA DI GIOCO ED ENTRATO, PER PURO CASO, NEL PRIMO DUNGEON.

È STATO AMORE, NON A PRIMA VISTA. C'È VOLUTO UN PO', MA DA QUEL TITOLO NON MI SONO MAI SEPARATO. 
ORA ECCOLO QUI, RIMASTERIZZATO PER SWITCH. 
OVVIAMENTE DOVEVA ESSERE MIO, IN COLLECTOR EDITION CHE DA BUON OSSESSIVO COMPULSIVO NON APRIRÒ.

RICORDO NITIDAMENTE QUEI GIORNI E NON RICORDO COSA HO MANGIATO PER CENA IERI.
QUESTO È PER FARVI CAPIRE COME RAGIONA IL MIO CERVELLO.

QUESTA VOLTA, LINK, NON POTRÒ PORTARTI VIA DA QUELL'ISOLA. POTRÒ FARLO SE TROVO UNA COPIA USATA 😅

Yesterday I finally visited Nintendo's office in Portugal! When I think about it, my life has been pretty crazy these last 2 years, younger me wouldn't believe the opportunities I'm getting. Thank you @nintendopt 💛💛💛
I was there to try out the new Nintendo Switch Lite which looks super cute and turns me into an irrational human being for wanting to buy it. I have already decided to buy the original Nintendo Switch because that's the only way I can stream. Nonetheless, this is a great alternative for anyone focusing on portability and want a cheaper, smaller and lighter Switch. I was worried it would feel too plastic, but no no no!
